The paper discusses a digital self-interference cancellation technique for full-duplex systems, which involves signal processing, communication networks, and system engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of data compression, communication, and cryptography. The second likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which covers the design, implementation, and evaluation of computer networks and communication protocols. The third likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which focuses on the modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems. The fourth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), which deals with the processing, analysis, and retrieval of multimedia data. The fifth likely category is cs.COM (Computers and Society), which covers the social and ethical aspects of computing and communication technologies.
